        <h2>
            <a class="text" asp-area="" asp-controller="Home" asp-action="caracas"><strong>Caracas -  ablessing and a curse</strong></a>
        </h2>
        <div1 classname="image-container">
            <img id="caracas" src="https://www.kayak.pl/rimg/dimg/cf/40/a5abdc30-city-990-1658b9a405e.jpg?width=1366&height=768&xhint=2112&yhint=1018&crop=true" />
        </div1>
        <div>
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>Caracas is the capital and largest city of Venezuela. It is located in the northern part of the country, in the Venezuelan coastal mountain range. With a population of over 3 million people, Caracas is a bustling metropolis that offers a unique blend of modernity and history.</p>
        </div>
        <h2>Top Attractions</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Mount Avila:</strong> A popular hiking destination with stunning views of the city.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>The National Pantheon:</strong> A historic church that contains the remains of several Venezuelan heroes and presidents.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>La Plaza Bolivar:</strong> A beautiful square surrounded by historic buildings and monuments.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Travel Information</h2>
        <div class="highlight">
            <p>The official language of Venezuela is Spanish, so English speakers may want to brush up on a few key phrases before traveling. The currency in Venezuela is the Bolivar Fuerte. Credit cards are widely accepted, but it's always a good idea to have some local currency on hand for smaller vendors and tips.</p>
            <p>Caracas is served by Simon Bolivar International Airport, which is located about 20 miles from the city center. There are several transportation options available from the airport, including taxis, buses, and rental cars.</p>
        </div>
