            <h2>
                <a class="text" asp-area="" asp-controller="Home" asp-action="philippines"><strong>Philippines - a paradise of 7,000 islands</strong></a>
            </h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img id="philippines" src="https://i.natgeofe.com/n/04505c35-858b-4e95-a1a7-d72e5418b7fc/steep-karst-cliffs-of-el-nido-in-palawan.jpg" />
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2>Introduction</h2>
                <p>The Philippines is an archipelago of over 7,000 islands in Southeast Asia. It is known for its stunning beaches, rich biodiversity, and vibrant culture. The capital city, Manila, is a bustling metropolis that offers a unique blend of modernity and history, while the rural areas of the country offer a glimpse into traditional Filipino life.</p>
            </div>
            <h2>Top Attractions</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Boracay:</strong> A small island in the Visayas region known for its powdery white sand beaches and crystal-clear waters.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Palawan:</strong> An island province in the western part of the country known for its stunning natural beauty, including limestone cliffs, lagoons, and underwater caves.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Chocolate Hills:</strong> A geological formation in Bohol made up of over 1,000 cone-shaped hills that turn brown during the dry season.
                </li>
            </ul>
            <h2>Travel Information</h2>
            <div class="highlight">
                <p>The official language of the Philippines is Filipino, but English is widely spoken throughout the country. The currency in the Philippines is the Philippine Peso. Credit cards are widely accepted in urban areas, but it's always a good idea to have some local currency on hand for smaller vendors and tips.</p>
                <p>The Philippines is served by several international airports, including Ninoy Aquino International Airport in Manila and Mactan-Cebu International Airport in Cebu. There are several transportation options available from the airport, including taxis, buses, and ride-sharing services.</p>
            </div>
